# Approach
We maintain two flags ```f1``` and ```f2``` for each player. Whenever we see a 10 for a player, we set the corresponding flag to 2. We also keep decrementing the flag at each turn. If the value of the flag is greater than 0 at a particular turn, it indicates the that player had scored a 10 in one of his two previous turns.

Thanks to @kreakEmp for this approach. Here's his [solution](https://leetcode.com/problems/determine-the-winner-of-a-bowling-game/solutions/3468463/explained-very-simple-easy-to-understand-solution/). 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(1)

# Code

##### Approach 1 :

```
class Solution {
    public int isWinner(int[] player1, int[] player2) {
        int n = player1.length;
        int p1Score = 0;
        int p2Score = 0;
        int f1 = 0;
        int f2 = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            p1Score += f1 > 0 ? 2*player1[i] : player1[i];
            f1--;
            p2Score += f2 > 0 ? 2*player2[i] : player2[i];
            f2--;
            if(player1[i] == 10) {
                f1 = 2;
            }
            if(player2[i] == 10) {
                f2 = 2;
            }
        }
        if(p1Score > p2Score) {
            return 1;
        } else if(p2Score > p1Score) {
            return 2;
        } else {
            return 0;
        }
    }
}
```

##### Approach 2 :
An alternate straightforward, readable solution
```
class Solution {
    public int isWinner(int[] player1, int[] player2) {
        int n = player1.length;
        int p1Score = 0;
        int p2Score = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            int p1TurnScore = player1[i];
            int p2TurnScore = player2[i];
            if(i == 1) { // at index 1, we can only check index 0 for a 10 score
                if(player1[0] == 10) {
                    p1TurnScore *= 2;
                }
                if(player2[0] == 10) {
                    p2TurnScore *= 2;
                }
            } else if(i-2 >= 0) { // index 2 onwards, we can check the previous 2 indices for 10s
                if(player1[i-1] == 10 || player1[i-2] == 10) {
                    p1TurnScore *= 2;
                }
                if(player2[i-1] == 10 || player2[i-2] == 10) {
                    p2TurnScore *= 2;
                }
            }
            p1Score += p1TurnScore;
            p2Score += p2TurnScore;
        }
        if(p1Score > p2Score) {
            return 1;
        } else if(p2Score > p1Score) {
            return 2;
        } else {
            return 0;
        }
    }
}
```

