# Intuition
###### In this problem we need to find the first row or column to be fully painted, so we can think of iterating over the array checking each time whether any row or column is fully painted or not.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
1. First we declare 2 frequency vectors for checking whether the row or column is fully painted or not and a map.

2. Now in order to check for every row or column for fully painted we can use a map to store the index of row and column simultaneouly corresponding to the element value. 

For Eg.   m[1] = {0, 0} meaning for the value of element 1 we store the index of row and column i.e. 0.

3. When iterating the array we keep updating the index of the row and the column in their corresponding frequency vectors.

4. After each updation we check whether the frequency of any row vector element equals to column size or vice versa. 

5. After it becomes equal we just simply return the index of that particular iteration.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(m*n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n) + O(n) + O(m*n)$$
