# Intuition
If we have multiple paths then why not try all?
**A->B (A->start and B->target coordinates)
A->s1->B
A->s2->B**
... so on
and even after going till s1 we could also go to some other special road like:-
**A->s1->s3->s4->B**

# Approach
For implementing it use a hashmap for keeping track of visited positions with the cost **(such that we will only consider those paths which are leading to a position in minimum time or cost)**

Rest code is easy to understand. Please give it a read!! :)
**And consider upvoting if you like the approach**

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int myWay(int[] start,int[] target,int[][] special)
    {
        HashMap<String,Integer> visited = new HashMap<>();
        Queue<int[]> queue = new ArrayDeque<>();
        queue.add(new int[]{start[0],start[1],0});//current row,col,cost so far till here
        visited.put(start[0]+"-"+start[1],0);//have reached till here with cost 0..so agar koi better hoga isse tohi lenge
        int minCost = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        while(queue.isEmpty()==false)
        {
            int[] curr = queue.poll();
            if(curr[2] >= minCost) continue;

            //case 1 - reach target from here only
            int costTillTarget = curr[2]+Math.abs(target[0]-curr[0]) + Math.abs(target[1]-curr[1]);
            minCost = Math.min(minCost,costTillTarget);

            //case 2- reach other special roads
            for(int i=0;i<special.length;i++)
            {
                int x1 = special[i][0];
                int y1 = special[i][1];
                int x2 = special[i][2];
                int y2 = special[i][3];
                int cost = special[i][4];
                int costTillx2y2 = curr[2] + Math.abs(curr[0]-x1)+Math.abs(curr[1]-y1) + cost;
                String pos = x2+" and "+y2;
                if(visited.containsKey(pos) && visited.get(pos) <= costTillx2y2) continue;//as then no improvement is there 
                //since we have reached till here with better price already at some point of time
                visited.put(pos,costTillx2y2);
                queue.offer(new int[]{x2,y2,costTillx2y2});
            }   
        }
        return minCost;
    }
    public int minimumCost(int[] start, int[] target, int[][] specialRoads) {
        return myWay(start,target,specialRoads);
    }
}
