# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Build a fully-connected graph for all the mentioned coordinates including the starting point and target. Then run Dijkstra algorithm from the starting point to target.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Technical detail on how to represent the graph: since the graph is fully connected, using a adjacency matrix of size `n x n` is feasible. We only have to update entries where the cost of the special road is smaller than the Manhattan distance between them.

How to get a fingerprint of a coordinate(x, y): since x and y range from 1 to 100000, we cannot generate a unique fingerprint using a 32-bit integer($10^{10} > (1<<32)$). However, we can use a size_t as the fingerprint by left shifting x coordinate by 32 bit and add y coordinate.

Optimization: if the cost of a special road is less than the Manhattan distance, we don't have to add this edge and need not to memorize the coordinate for them.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Building the graph: takes $O(n^2)$. The worst case is all the nodes are unique and the special roads are shorter than the Manhattan distance between them.

Run Dijkstra: $O(n + n^2\log(n)) = O(n^2\log n)$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$O(n^2)$ for the graph.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumCost(vector<int>& start, vector<int>& target,
                    vector<vector<int>>& specialRoads) {
        // Check trivial edge case.
        if (start == target) return 0;
        int res = abs(start[0] - target[0]) + abs(start[1] - target[1]);

        // Add starting point and target.
        add_node(start[0], start[1]);
        add_node(target[0], target[1]);

        // Add all unique points.
        for (auto & v: specialRoads) {
            int x = v[0], y = v[1], s = v[2], t = v[3], c = v[4];
            if (abs(x-s) + abs(y-t) <= c) continue;
            add_node(x, y);
            add_node(s, t);
        } 

        // Build the fully-connected graph.
        int n = node_list.size();
        graph = vector<vector<int>> (n, vector<int>(n, INT_MAX));

        // Update the shortcuts for the uni-directed graph.
        for (auto & v: specialRoads) {
            int x = v[0], y = v[1], s = v[2], t = v[3], c = v[4];
            if (abs(x-s) + abs(y-t) <= c) continue;
            int id1 = node_map[make_key(x, y)];
            int id2 = node_map[make_key(s, t)];
            graph[id1][id2] = min(graph[id1][id2], c);
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                if (graph[i][j] == INT_MAX) {
                    graph[i][j] = abs(node_list[i].first - node_list[j].first) +
                                  abs(node_list[i].second - node_list[j].second);
                }
            }
        }

        // Dijkstra Algorithm.
        dist.assign(n, INT_MAX);
        dist[0] = 0;

        // pq: (dist, id)
        priority_queue<pair<int, int>, vector<pair<int, int>>, greater<pair<int, int>>> pq;
        pq.push({0, 0});

        while (!pq.empty()) {
            auto [d, id] = pq.top(); pq.pop();
            // Check if popped coordinate is target.
            if (id == 1) return d;
            // Check if the current shortest distance is out of date.
            if (dist[id] < d) continue;
            // Check neighbors.
            for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
                if (i == id) continue;
                if (dist[i] > d + graph[id][i]) {
                    dist[i] = d + graph[id][i];
                    pq.push({dist[i], i});
                }
            }
        }
        // Should not reach here.
        return res;

    }

private:

    // Generate fingerprint for the coordinate (x, y), left shift x by 32 bit and
    // add y.
    inline size_t make_key(size_t x, size_t y) {return (x<<32)|y;}

    // Check if (x, y) already exists in the node_list.
    // If not, append (x, y) to the node list and assign the index to it.    
    void add_node(int x, int y) {
        size_t k = make_key(x, y);
        if (node_map.count(k)) return;
        int index = node_map[k] = node_list.size();
        node_list.push_back({x, y});
    }

    vector<pair<int, int>> node_list;      // Store all the coordinates.
    unordered_map<size_t, int> node_map;   // From unique key to index.
    vector<vector<int>> graph;             // Store distances between node i and j.
    vector<int> dist;                      // Store minimal distance from the starting point.

};
```

