# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Construct a new graph with the special roads and new distances as edges.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Each special road can have atmost 2 unique endpoints. Therefore in total 200*2+2 = 402 total unique points.
No of nodes in new graph = 402 = n;
No of edges in new graph atmax = m = n*(n-1)/2;

Hence time complexity of djikstra = O(mlog(n))

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n*n)

# Code
```
typedef vector<int> VI;
typedef vector<VI> VVI;

class Solution {
public:
    int djikstra(int source, int target, VVI &graph, VVI &edges){
        int n = graph.size();
        VI dis(n, INT_MAX);

        multiset<pair<int, int>> pq;
        pq.insert({source, 0});
        while(!pq.empty()){
            int node = pq.begin()->second, dist = pq.begin()->first;
            pq.erase(pq.begin());

            if(node == target) return dist;

            if(dis[node] > dist) dis[node] = dist;
            else continue;

            for(auto x: graph[node]){
                if(dis[x] == INT_MAX){
                    pq.insert({dist + edges[node][x], x});
                }
            }
        }
        return dis[target];
    }
