# Intuition
we can think this question is to ask to find Shortest Paths from Source to target through middles vertices using Dijkstra’s Algorithm. The variant is that we pick two vertices ($x1_i$, $y1_i$), ($x2_i$, $y2_i$) once a time if we choose one special road `i` with cost $cost_i$, where. ($x1_i$, $y1_i$) is the start vertice of the spcecial road, and ($x2_i$, $y2_i$) is the end vertice.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Q: how to find shortest path like 

Start -> ($x1_i$, $y1_i$) -> ($x2_i$, $y2_i$) ->  ($x1_{j}$, $y1_{j}$) -> ($x2_{j}$, $y2_{j}$) -> ...-> Target


The key idea is 
-  store costs from start vertice to all end point ($x2_i$, $y2_i$) in special roads into an array `d`; store index of that covered special road into a priority queue, and later to go through all items in that queue. Formular is as folllow: 
  d[i] = abs($x1_i$ - start[0]) + abs($y1_i$ - start[1]) + $cost_i$

- The cost from ($x2_i$, $y2_i$) to the final target vertice is
  abs(target[1] - $y2_i$) + abs(target[0] - $x2_i$)

- The cost for S -> $x_i$ -> T is equal to 
  cur_cost = d[i] +  abs(target[1] - $y2_i$) + abs(target[0] - $x2_i$); 
  then compare the min cost from S to T through $road_i$ with the one from S to T without $road_i$

- And then start from $x_i$, calculate its cost to other end vertice `j` in other special roads; if  `d[i]` + cost from  ($x1_i$, $y1_i$) to ($x2_j$, $y2_j$) smaller than the orginal `d[j]`, update d[j]. put `j` into the priority queue. 



# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(V^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity: O(V)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
  int minimumCost(vector<int>& start, vector<int>& target, vector<vector<int>>& specialRoads) {        
        int ans = abs(target[1] - start[1]) + abs(target[0] - start[0]);
        vector<int> d(specialRoads.size(), 0);
        priority_queue<int> pq;

        for(int i = 0; i < specialRoads.size(); i++) {
            d[i] = abs(specialRoads[i][1] - start[1]) + abs(specialRoads[i][0] - start[0]) + specialRoads[i][4];
            pq.push(i);
        }

        while(!pq.empty()) {
            int idx = pq.top(); pq.pop(); 

            vector<int> sr = specialRoads[idx];
            ans = min(ans, d[idx] + abs(target[1] - sr[3]) + abs(target[0] - sr[2]));

            for(int j = 0; j < specialRoads.size(); j++) {
                if(j == idx) continue;
                int w = abs(specialRoads[j][1] - sr[3]) + abs(specialRoads[j][0] - sr[2]) + specialRoads[j][4];
                if(d[idx] + w < d[j]) {
                    d[j] = d[idx] + w; 
                    pq.push(j);
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
