# Intuition
Use Dijistra's to solve the problem

# Approach
We have to travel from start to target using road, so add the special roads to edges. Also add the normal distances of each vertices to other to edges as that might be used to edges.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(V + ElogE), here V = number of vertices equals to number of special roads and Edges equal to n + n*n. So, TC: $$O(n^2logn)$$
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n^2)$$, due to edgeList being stored

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumCost(int[] start, int[] target, int[][] specialRoads) {
   List<int[]> points = new ArrayList<>();
   points.add(new int[]{start[0], start[1]});
   Map<Integer, List<int[]>> edgeMap = new HashMap<>();

   int idx = 1;
   for(int[] specialRoad: specialRoads){
      points.add(new int[]{specialRoad[0], specialRoad[1]});
      points.add(new int[]{specialRoad[2], specialRoad[3]});
      if(!edgeMap.containsKey(idx)){
        edgeMap.put(idx, new ArrayList<>());
      }
      edgeMap.get(idx).add(new int[]{idx + 1, specialRoad[4]});

      idx += 2;
   }

   points.add(new int[]{target[0], target[1]});
   for(int i = 0; i < points.size(); i++){
      for(int j = i + 1; j < points.size(); j++){
        if(!edgeMap.containsKey(i)){
            edgeMap.put(i, new ArrayList<>());
        }
        edgeMap.get(i).add(new int[]{j, Math.abs(points.get(i)[0] - points.get(j)[0]) + Math.abs(points.get(i)[1] - points.get(j)[1])});
        if(!edgeMap.containsKey(j)){
            edgeMap.put(j, new ArrayList<>());
        }
        edgeMap.get(j).add(new int[]{i, Math.abs(points.get(i)[0] - points.get(j)[0]) + Math.abs(points.get(i)[1] - points.get(j)[1])});
     }
   }

  int[] minDist = new int[points.size()];
  Arrays.fill(minDist, -1);

  PriorityQueue<int[]> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((p1, p2) ->{
    return p1[1] - p2[1];
  });

  pq.add(new int[]{0, 0});

  while(!pq.isEmpty()){
     int[] edge = pq.remove();
     int v = edge[0];
     int dist = edge[1];

     if(minDist[v] == -1){
        minDist[v] = dist;
        for(int[] ed: edgeMap.get(v)){
            pq.add(new int[]{ed[0], dist + ed[1]});
        }
     } 
  }

  return minDist[points.size() - 1];

}
}
```

