# Intuition
Path to special Roads and Path to Target. These will be the entry in the Priority Queue. We can also start with looking adjacent cordinates with a dist as 1. But reaching via special roads will be less if we move by 1 dist at a time. SO this gives me an idea to elimiate them and directly use special path.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
O(m) to build the Map for look up of special path // lets say m special paths
O(m + mlog(m)) 


- Space complexity:
O(m * k) k is the length of the shortest path
# Code
```
class Solution {
     int r []= {0,-1,1,0};
    int c []= {1,0,0,-1};
    class P {
        int x;
        int y;
        int cost;

        @Override
        public String toString() {
            return x + " &&& " + y +  " &&& " +cost;
        }
    }
    public int minimumCost(int[] start, int[] target, int[][] specialRoads) {


        int res = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        PriorityQueue<P> pq = new PriorityQueue<>(new Comparator<P>() {

            @Override
            public int compare(P a, P b) {
                return a.cost - b.cost; // min heap and 0 element is the cost and 1 and 2  is the index.
            }
        });

        Map<String,  List<int[]>> special = new HashMap<>();
        for(int [] s : specialRoads) {
            String hj = s[0] + "##" + s[1];

            if(special.containsKey(hj)) {
                special.get(hj).add( new int[] {s[2],s[3], s[4]});
            } else {
                List<int[]> l = new ArrayList<>();
                l.add( new int[] {s[2],s[3], s[4]});
                special.put(hj, l);
            }


        }
        P st = new P();
        st.x = start[0];
        st.y = start[1];
        st.cost = 0;
        pq.add(st);
        Set<String> visisted = new HashSet<>();


        while(pq.size() > 0) {

            P p1 = pq.poll();

            if(p1.x == target[0] && p1.y == target[1]) {
                return p1.cost;
            }

             String gh = p1.x + "##" + p1.y;
             if(visisted.contains(gh)) continue;
             visisted.add(gh);


            for(Map.Entry<String,  List<int[]>> entry : special.entrySet()) {
                int d = Math.abs(p1.x - Integer.valueOf(entry.getKey().split("##")[0])) + 
                Math.abs(p1.y - Integer.valueOf(entry.getKey().split("##")[1]));
                 for(int[] cos :  entry.getValue()) {
                     P p = new P();
                     p.x = cos[0];
                     p.y = cos[1];
                     p.cost = d + cos[2] + p1.cost;
                    pq.add(p);

                 }


            }

                 P p2 = new P();
                p2.x = target[0];
                p2.y = target[1];
                p2.cost = Math.abs(target[0] - p1.x) + Math.abs(target[1] -p1.y) + p1.cost;
                pq.add(p2);







        }

        return -1;
    }
}
